Colin Plumb (colin@nyx10.cs.du.edu) wrote:
: If you read the RSAREF licence, it requires that the distributor of an
: Application Program using RSAREF get IN WRITING from each recipient
: guarnatees that they will not use RSAREF (and thus the whole program)
: commercially (as defined by the RSAREF licence, which is a bit looser than
: some obvious definitions).

: This is a pretty awkward burden for something that's supposed to be
: available by FTP and so on.

This condition does not appear in any recent version of the
RSAREF license.  I seem to recall that it did appear in a 
very early version of the license.
